WEBVTT

00:02.074 --> 00:03.808
Dalton! Dalton! Dalton!

00:06.345 --> 00:09.748
Dalton! Dalton! Dalton!

00:09.749 --> 00:11.183
Thank you.

00:11.184 --> 00:15.521
You know, I once had a
basketball coach who said,

00:15.522 --> 00:17.390
"You want to win,
get the ball in the hoop."

00:17.391 --> 00:19.392
I'd...

00:19.393 --> 00:21.527
like to say the season I spent
as the starting forward

00:21.528 --> 00:24.063
for the Hamilton High
Tigers was a winning one,

00:24.064 --> 00:29.168
but, I'm afraid wewe didn't
get enough balls in hoops.

00:29.169 --> 00:31.571
But that season, I found something

00:31.572 --> 00:33.072
I didn't know I'd been looking for.

00:33.073 --> 00:36.643
That feeling of coming together
with a group of people

00:36.644 --> 00:38.611
who had your back.

00:38.612 --> 00:41.981
All of us trying to bring
out the best in each other.

00:41.982 --> 00:47.053
I, can see now that my
journey to public service

00:47.054 --> 00:51.958
began with that failed season
on the Hamilton Tigers.

00:53.360 --> 00:58.131
Now, though my season in
politics may be ending...

01:00.234 --> 01:04.337
my journey in public
service never will.

01:04.337 --> 01:07.340
Nor should it for any of you.

01:07.341 --> 01:10.009
So let's all keep
fighting for a strong,

01:10.010 --> 01:13.880
prosperous and secure California
for generations to come.

01:13.881 --> 01:17.750
It's been an honor, truly.

01:17.751 --> 01:20.420
God bless the great
state of California.

01:20.421 --> 01:21.954
And God bless all of you.

01:21.955 --> 01:23.990
Thank you.

01:23.991 --> 01:26.259
Dalton! Dalton!

01:26.260 --> 01:29.362
Dalton! Dalton! Dalton!

01:29.363 --> 01:34.667
Dalton! Dalton! Dalton!

01:34.668 --> 01:36.135
- You have my vote, sir.
- Thank you. Thanks for being here.

01:36.136 --> 01:37.804
Keep fighting. Appreciate it.

01:37.805 --> 01:40.006
Ben. Sorry to break
your winning streak.

01:40.007 --> 01:42.141
Yeah, should've had this one, Conrad.

01:42.142 --> 01:44.811
Well, you ran a crack team.

01:44.812 --> 01:47.013
Already off to the next rodeo?

01:47.014 --> 01:49.215
Delaware house seat special election.

01:49.216 --> 01:50.650
He's not half the candidate you are,

01:50.651 --> 01:53.353
but if he manages to not skip
the debate at the last minute,

01:53.354 --> 01:56.289
we might have a shot.

01:56.290 --> 01:58.257
Go get 'em.

01:58.258 --> 02:00.860
You, too.

02:00.861 --> 02:03.096
All righty, Mr. President.

02:03.097 --> 02:05.598
Hope you're not too nervous
for the big final exam.

02:05.599 --> 02:07.667
My colleagues are
starting to fight over

02:07.668 --> 02:10.370
who deserves credit for
your amazing recovery.

02:10.371 --> 02:12.038
I'm sure you'll pass
with flying colors.

02:13.374 --> 02:15.241
And here comes Russell,
to make sure I don't cheat.

02:15.242 --> 02:16.409
I can come back later.

02:16.410 --> 02:17.543
Stay.

02:17.544 --> 02:18.711
He's good with an audience.
Something about

02:18.712 --> 02:20.046
being the leader of the free world.

02:20.047 --> 02:22.715
Soon to be.

02:22.716 --> 02:24.684
If all goes well.

02:24.685 --> 02:25.952
No pressure.

02:25.953 --> 02:27.787
I'm gonna say five
words, and I want you

02:27.788 --> 02:29.155
to repeat them back to me.

02:29.156 --> 02:32.492
"Baby, monkey, glass, sunset, iron."

02:32.493 --> 02:34.861
"Baby, monkey, glass, sunset, iron."

02:34.862 --> 02:36.162
Good. Now, backwards?

02:36.163 --> 02:39.197
"Iron, sunset, glass, monkey, baby."

02:42.002 --> 02:43.302
Well done, sir.

02:43.303 --> 02:45.304
Not sure I could remember all that.

02:45.305 --> 02:48.674
I'm firing on all ganglia,
so I'm told.

02:48.675 --> 02:50.843
Once we, get the official results,

02:50.844 --> 02:52.912
we'll just need you to
sign a letter to Congress,

02:52.913 --> 02:55.114
ending your temporary medical leave,

02:55.115 --> 02:57.116
and we're good to go.

02:57.117 --> 03:00.420
I'll be happy to get back
to security briefings.

03:00.421 --> 03:02.121
Why does anyone watch cable news?

03:03.223 --> 03:05.458
First order of business
will be a ceremony

03:05.459 --> 03:07.460
to present the Presidential
Medal of Freedom

03:07.461 --> 03:09.862
to the newly elected
president of Myanmar.

03:09.863 --> 03:11.731
U Khaing.

03:11.732 --> 03:13.099
Ten years in prison, and now

03:13.100 --> 03:15.234
he's their first
democraticallyelected president

03:15.235 --> 03:16.702
in over 50 years.

03:16.703 --> 03:17.770
Yeah.

03:17.771 --> 03:19.439
Very popular on cable news.

03:19.440 --> 03:22.208
Well, the ceremony will
generate a lot of coverage.

03:22.209 --> 03:24.610
It'll be a fitting welcome...
and welcome back...

03:24.611 --> 03:28.848
to two valued leaders of democracy.

03:28.849 --> 03:32.117
Well, let's see how
the tests come out.

03:37.758 --> 03:39.192
- Morning.
- Hey.

03:39.193 --> 03:40.960
Do you have time for a muffin?

03:40.961 --> 03:42.962
What life would I be living

03:42.963 --> 03:44.997
if I didn't have time for a muffin?

03:44.998 --> 03:47.033
Not your best one.

03:47.034 --> 03:48.601
Hey, you were up late last night.

03:48.602 --> 03:50.136
Yeah, I have an antiquities final.

03:50.137 --> 03:52.138
I'm seeing togas in my sleep.

03:52.139 --> 03:53.706
I'll pick you up at the
train station, Maureen.

03:53.707 --> 03:54.674
It's not a big deal.

03:54.675 --> 03:56.342
Aunt Maureen is coming?

03:56.343 --> 03:57.977
Why don't you say that louder?
I don't think she heard you.

03:57.978 --> 03:59.879
- Sorry, I just didn't know.
- Okay. Bye.

03:59.880 --> 04:01.514
Yeah, it was kind of
a lastminute idea.

04:01.515 --> 04:03.131
There's an art exhibit in
town she wants to see.

04:03.132 --> 04:04.565
Aunt Maureen wants to
see an art exhibit?

04:04.566 --> 04:05.513
Hey.

04:05.514 --> 04:07.720
- What's that supposed to mean?
- I'm just surprised.

04:07.721 --> 04:09.055
- What is it?
- Renoir.

04:09.056 --> 04:10.195
- Well, that makes sense.
- Okay.

04:10.196 --> 04:11.285
You know what?

04:11.286 --> 04:12.925
- That is total elitism.
- You know, one year of art school,

04:12.926 --> 04:13.926
- and you're all, like...
- It is.

04:13.927 --> 04:15.620
I'm not being an elitist.

04:15.621 --> 04:18.557
It's just all of those rosy
cheeks and flowery fields

04:18.558 --> 04:21.495
- and little fluffy dogs.
- Now I just want to go with you.

04:21.495 --> 04:25.466
But I can't, because the
second most important visitor

04:25.467 --> 04:28.269
is landing in D.C. in
less than an hour.

04:28.270 --> 04:29.770
The new Burmese president.

04:29.771 --> 04:31.005
Yeah. U Khaing.

04:31.006 --> 04:32.206
That guy is so cool.

04:32.207 --> 04:33.874
He's like the Nelson
Mandela of Myanmar.

04:33.875 --> 04:34.976
Only, dreamy.

04:34.977 --> 04:37.378
Okay, the Dalai Lama
passed through town,

04:37.379 --> 04:38.980
and you didn't even look
up from your phone.

04:38.981 --> 04:40.448
And now we know why. Okay, bye.

04:40.449 --> 04:41.549
Hey, dinner.

04:41.550 --> 04:43.317
You know how Maureen is about takeout.

04:43.318 --> 04:44.652
Yes, yes, I will definitely
be here for dinner.

04:44.653 --> 04:46.120
- Yeah.
- Don't say "definitely."

04:46.121 --> 04:47.989
Don't say... you're gonna curse it.

04:47.990 --> 04:50.024
"Endeavor," then. I will
endeavor... ggoodbye.

04:50.025 --> 04:50.958
Okay, that's better.

04:50.959 --> 04:52.663
- Okay? Good luck.
- Okay, bye.

